    • basicSelfCheckRunner

      public static boolean basicSelfCheckRunner​(SelfCheckCapable item)
      Runs a self-check and pretty-print the result of the check. Note that the colors may not show correctly in some terminals. DO NOT USE THIS AS THE ACTUAL SELF-CHECK method! This will call self-check method of the item passed in, so if you call it from the self-check method you will end up creating an infinite recursion!
      Parameters:
      item - the item to be tested
      Returns:
      the colorized version of the run. Colors may not show in all terminals

    • checkComponents

      public static boolean checkComponents​(Object... items)
      This tester tests all componets that are provided as parameters. If any component is implemented as a GenericComponent, its subcomponents are also tested. Note that the count will only reflect the top-level components for the time being. SelfCheckUtils.checkComponents(wheels, sensors, camera);
      Parameters:
      items - A comma separated list of items - can be any object, but only those that implement SelfCheckCapable will be tested. Supports Arrays of SelfCheckCapable objects Supports Lists of SelfCheckCapable objects
      Returns:
      a single boolean result telling you if the final test was successful
